# Dragon System Bot Privacy Policy

Last Updated: June 2026

Dragon System Bot respects user privacy and only collects data necessary to provide its services.

Data that may be stored:

* Server IDs
* Channel IDs
* Role IDs
* User IDs
* Ticket information
* Application responses
* Moderation logs
* Warning records
* Bot configuration settings

Data is stored in JSON files on the bot's server and is used solely for operating the bot's features.

Dragon System Bot does not sell user data to third parties.

Dragon System Bot does not use stored data to train artificial intelligence or machine learning models.

Users may request data deletion by contacting the bot owner or server administrators through the server's support system.

Reasonable security measures are used to protect stored data.

This Privacy Policy may be updated from time to time.
